The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem in directed graphs (tournaments) and provides approximation and kernelization results. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization and algorithmic techniques. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with tournaments, which are a common object of study in game theory. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and its approximation and kernelization. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimization problems, which are relevant to AI applications.
